luorescence via\nin-vacuum or in-gas Total Internal Reflection Fluorescence Microscopy. We\npresent the status of this technique and the outlook for barium tagging with\nOn-Off switchable fluorophores, including new results with a\nBa$^{2+}$-selective dye that functions under our desired conditions in the\nvisible region and with single ion sensitivity.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Sep 2019 18:00:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-12"}
